                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.515 Gold Bloc/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-29T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 29, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Ryder on completion of his work at Geneva is visiting various countries for
                    the Tariff Commission in order to observe general trade and tariff situation. He
                    does not expect and is not authorized to discuss trade negotiations in London. I
                    am sure that he will say nothing to create misunderstanding of the purposes of
                    his visit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
